Morocco,pBcJZTjd3og,UgxGf6gYNZXhkv0Qnyp4AaABAg,,@Mariam-rx6re,"Why are we hating on koshari
It isn’t the best Egyptian food but its delicious nonetheless. 
It has a very deep story behind it and is very sentimental to Egyptians
Koshari is a dish that was made during the British occupation on egypt, it was the only thing Egyptians could afford at the time, it is high in carbs and protein to provide Egyptians energy to live at the time. It is not the national dish because it is the best one, but because of how it helped Egyptians to survive. 
