Tourism,cRdwAQD1OKE,Ugx2GX5YYGJ_gVmo9fh4AaABAg,,@peternewman9682,"I have been travelling to the Philippines since 2008 and finally relocated in 2020.

For everything that is said it is still cheaper than the UK, USA and Europe to visit or live.

Fuel did increase but unlike the UK tge givernment here as removed the tax bringing thr prices down, unlike the UK Goernment that keeps creaming it off and giving nothing back to the workers.

As for infrastructure there as been considerable improvements

 - widening the SLEX and increasing it to south Luzon

- new Calax almost completes from Luzon across to Cavite

- new road networks to the airport

- new metro lines open and extended

- understand the UK is worried with the new tourist taxes introduced - £135

- visa process in the Philippines is still cheaper and easier to navigate than other locations for real tourists

- NAIX and Clark airports have both been improved and ongoing

- currency concersion for GBP Increased from around 65php to £1 to currently in excess of 80php.

- fuel prices are still cheaper than the UK - good for tourists but a challenge for locals - still relatively cheaper than the UK

- I have lived outside the UK since 2007 and every where I have lived - the gullable tourists are taken advabtage of (from Egypt to Qatar, Dubai to Morocco) let alone places like Thailand, Malaysia, Indonesia, Singapore , Hong Kong.

Yes the country is not perfect but it is not as bad as people make out.",2026-04-23T08:55:04Z,2026-04-23T08:55:04Z,0,False,0.0,2026-04-27T02:02:28.221296
