Tourism,cRdwAQD1OKE,UgylEfEdf1virHtOYCJ4AaABAg,,@vfitcoach,"This perspective is very subjective.  I'm  a frequent visitor of the Philippines and somewhat a digital nomad.  Since I'm from California and the USD is strong against the PHP, so the extra costs are not significant enough to ruin a fantastic trip.   Big cities such as Manila and Cebu are congested and take longer to get to destinations, but there are so many other destinations where you won't feel a strain on your budget.      I've been to Thailand and other ASEAN countries and the biggest short coming of other ASEAN countries is the language barrier, that you won't experience in the Philippines.   Don't forget the super friendliness of the Philippine people   I believe tourists should still keep the Philippines as a top tourist option in South East Asia, just get there and the vast majority that do, will have no regrets on doing so.",2026-04-23T02:44:11Z,2026-04-23T02:44:11Z,4,False,0.0,2026-04-27T02:02:28.221415
