Tourism,cRdwAQD1OKE,UgzW9bHExR5E0oobIl54AaABAg,,@milpitians5621,"Reading some of the comments for this video, I feel they are a little too negative on the Philippines compared to my personal experience. I have currently been here for two months and plan to stay another three. I will be the first one to admit that most of the country is too polluted with bad infrastructure. I've been to five cities already where this is the case. However, in Iloilo, I have found it to be relatively clean, the power stays on, and the traffic isn't too terrible. Are there transactional people who only treat you well because they view you as a rich foreigner? Absolutely. But I have also made friends with people who don't care about money. They make their own. So it really depends on where you hangout and who you make friend with. In terms of being ripped off, I haven't experienced that at all since I don't eat at the food stalls. Every restaurant I've been to has a menu with listed prices, and I've ALWAYS paid the price that was listed, nothing more. I also take Grab taxis everywhere, which charges you a predefined amount before you book the ride. Getting around the country can be a pain, but it hasn't been a dealbreaker for me yet. I was surprised I could get from Moalboal to Iloilo without having to board an airplane. Buses and ferries did the trick. The prices of goods are increasing, but they are still extremely low compared to what I pay in the United States.

The one area that is a big problem is the rising fuel costs, as noted in this video. I have noticed that Grab trips are costing more now. Airline tickets to get here are also insane. They've nearly doubled. Originally, I had planed to leave in May and comeback in the fall. However, with soaring ticket prices, I've decided to just stay for the summer, then leave for the US in the fall and not return until the new year. I am afraid of what this will do to tourism in the Philippines. The people here are hardworking and resilient. But in the end, that doesn't put food on the table. Hopefully, the war will end soon and prices will start to drop.",2026-04-22T23:43:02Z,2026-04-22T23:43:02Z,2,False,1.0,2026-04-27T02:02:28.221466
