Tourism,cRdwAQD1OKE,UgzI52C7AB0MeoAHHTF4AaABAg,,@USBestCountryonEarth,"I really wanted to visit the Philippines and possibly stay there long term (as a digital nomad) but some things changed my mind. After hearing about the massive corruption in government and law enforcement, the poor unfair treatment of tourists, and the overly priced accomodations, the value for the price of visiting the Philippines fell drastically. 

At the minimum I want to know the Filipino government would have my back if I was falsely accused or framed for a crime. That I would receive fair legal due process. Instead, I hear horror stories of foreign men who were falsely accused of SA and imprisoned. The foreigner is treated as a second class citizen compared to the local Filipino. 

The legal authorities prioritize financially extorting the foreigner versus giving fair due process. There was a case where a foreigner from the USA was accused of SA by his crazy ex girlfriend who he separated from for many months. The police arrested him based on zero evidence and he was waiting in prison for 2 years for his trial. In the mean time, the ex girlfriend tried to extort massive sums of money from him so she would drop the charges. How the hell is this even legal?!! He had zero rights in prison and his health suffered. In the end no evidence was found of SA and he was still convicted because of some bullcrap law of arguing with his ex GF at some point. This law is arbitrarily applied to mainly foreigner men instead of locals. He was then deported and blacklisted from re-entering the country. 

Another tourist had a vehicle accident (which was not his fault) and the police sided with the local driver immediately. He had to prove his innocence from video footage. So the foreigner is immediately suspected to be guilty if something occurs. This type of treatment of foreigners makes me disgusted. I don't want to be looked at as a juicy wallet to be squeezed and disposed of. I want respect and fair treatment AT A MINIMUM. 

The internet sees and hears about these real life experiences and remembers. It puts people off and its sobering. 

Besides the main issue of corruption and poor treatment, the price of tourist attractions and accomodations is too high compared to surrounding countries. In addition there are many different small fees that are charged from the tourist which never serve their intended purpose. A fee to enter a beach that is never maintained. A ""environmental charge"" fee to snorkle or scuba dive that is never used to treat the environment. 
Majority of those fees are a scam to provide a revenue stream for corrupt politicians. 

NO THANKS. Ill PASS.",2026-04-22T20:55:10Z,2026-04-22T20:55:10Z,34,False,12.0,2026-04-27T02:02:28.221548
