AFCON,Rv93fEzUe_g,UgwqeUjBG8V0JcyJ0px4AaABAg,,@LahlouAbde-f7j3n,"The Senegalese national team displayed a blatant lack of respect towards the FIFA president, the CAF president, the tournament organizing committee, and the senior sports officials present at the stadium during the final match between Senegal and Morocco, the host country of the 2025 CAF World Cup in the Kingdom of Morocco. The players left the pitch for the locker room for approximately fifteen minutes. They may have showered, had a drink, or used their phones before returning to finish the match with utter insolence and disrespect. Their entry and exit from the pitch mid-match, without any legal basis, freely and without sanction, constitute the greatest disgrace in the history of world football. Furthermore, they provoked unrest and clashes between Senegalese supporters and Moroccan security forces, tarnishing what was arguably the best and most impressive tournament ever held in Africa. However, these actions were orchestrated and instigated by parties hostile to Morocco in order to sabotage Moroccan and continental celebrations. Therefore, severe sanctions are necessary, and the law must be enforced. This should serve as a lesson for the future of African and world football.",2026-01-30T22:42:19Z,2026-01-30T22:42:19Z,0,False,0.0,2026-04-27T02:03:07.672854
