CAN,4Eg_di-O8nM,Ugzs137TyuMHn93b4Ct4AaABAg,,@DanielCollins._,"My sermon notes for  "" You Can Change The End "" 


1.) You can't get a fresh start, but you can take a forward step. Big door swing on little hinges


2.) You may say it's over, Moses says to stand still, God says to move on. 


3.) Small decisions can be a gate to big opportunities. One letter, small actions, tiny decisions can lead to big doors. But what is your response when you are not in control? Hinge moments change destiny. God is placing you at hinge moments constantly. But it is up to you on how you respond to what God is giving you. You can go back, stand still, or move forward. Sometimes your decisions are made within doubt. Allow those decision be an opportunity to step up to what Is next rather than bail from what God is providing you. Beware of any word from God, that pulls you toward an escape from reality rather than an embrace from responsibillty. Freedom doesn't necessarily mean relief from what you have already decided


4.) If you keep looking for your version of ""better"", you won't always see what God is placing right in front of you. Perspective is subjective reality! It is how you look! And what you see. You might not make lt, GOD SAYS MOVE ON, stop listening to the LIAR, GOD'S GOT THIS AND HE'S GOT YOU. 
5.) You may criticize yourself, see your failures, lose joy, and feel this is the end. Are you responding like Moses or Iistening to God? You might not make it If you stand still like Moses. What you need for the next season is at God's feet who is moving forward. 


6.) Do you believe this is the end?
Or are you willing to move forward—
and see what’s still coming?
What, then? Are you looking at your decisions from your perspective or God's perspective? It never has to end like It is right now. You can't fix the beginning, but you can change the end if you move on like God. Once you change your perspective to see what God is showing you, there will always be a better opportunity for the next chapter of your life. Your story is never over.

7.) How do you want this to end? God is always presenting opportunities for you to change what's next. Which ""then"" will you take? Be weary of who you are listening to, yourself or God, when it comes to choosing the next chapter of your story. The results belongs to God, the response belongs to you. Stand up, have faith in yourself that God is providing you the right response for where you need to go.",2026-04-26T20:01:34Z,2026-04-26T20:01:34Z,41,False,7.0,2026-04-27T02:04:21.530153
